snippet.textDisplay: Debate me if you think I’m wrong. I believe we’re not really in control of exposing our lower lat. I think it’s far more genetic. I’m not saying we can’t make our lower lat come out a little more. I’m saying it’ll overexpose your whole upper lat even more if you try to get your lower lat to expose hard, making your problem bigger if you’re insecure like me of the upper lat making you look like one of those weirdos who overdo muscle gain. I think it’s going to depend on our rib cage and how the muscle is stretched around our serratus. In English, our lat muscles kinda wraps around our mid upper ribs rather than hangs wide out like a wing. It’s normal for lats to give off a wing illusion but it’s their thickness and shape wrapping around that gives it the wing look. Look at anybody’s lats from different angles. I think the chances of getting evened out perfect upper and lower lats (like C. Ronaldo, Justin Bieber or Bruce Lee) are about the same as getting straight teeth when your teeth are crowded (I’m a victim of that too). Debate me please. I hope I’m wrong. I want my lower lats to look mean too haha
